---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <p class="mt-4 lg:mt-0">
        Based in Manila, I love building things that actually make a difference
        from scalable backend and generative ai systems to creative side
        projects. I'm also an open-source contributor who enjoys sharing what I
        learn and collaborating with the developer community.
    </p>
    <p class="my-4">
        I started coding at 15, writing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript on my phone.
        That early curiosity pushed me beyond the web and into low-level
        projects like building compilers and creating my own programming
        language,{" "}
        <a
            class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
            href="https://github.com/decimozs/hiraya"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
            @Hiraya
        </a>
        . Along the way, I discovered my love for backend and ai engineering for building
        systems that solve real-world problems.
    </p>
<p class="my-4">
        I believe in minimalist, functional engineering. As systems grow
        complex, architecture must stay lean for security, governance, and
        horizontal scalability.
    </p>
    <p class="my-4">
        I'm deeply curious about how production-grade engineers solve complex
        problems.{" "}
        <a
            href="https://www.pragmaticengineer.com/"
            class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
            @The Pragmatic Engineer
        </a>
        {" "}is a cornerstone of my technical diet. This habit shapes my philosophy:
        autonomous agents and distributed workflows must be engineered for scale,
        security, and real-world impact.
    </p>
    <p>
        Currently, I'm a remote Backend Engineer and AI Engineer Intern,
        exploring LLM architectures. Outside code, I'm a dedicated runner
training for an upcoming marathon.
    </p>
    <p class="my-4">
        To learn more about my background and professional experience, you can
        view my{" "}
        <a
            href="/resume.pdf"
            class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            id="resume-link"
        >
            resume
        </a>
        . Additionally, to see my work in action, feel free to browse my{" "}
        <a
            href="/works"
            class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
        >
            works
        </a>
        , explore my contributions on{" "}
        <a
            href="https://github.com/decimozs"
            class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            id="github-profile-link"
        >
            @github.com/decimozs
        </a>
        , or connect with me on{" "}
        <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/decimomartin/"
            class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            id="linkedin-profile-link"
        >
            @linkedin.com/in/decimomartin
        </a>
        .
    </p>
</Layout>

<script is:inline>
    document
        .getElementById("resume-link")
        ?.addEventListener("click", function () {
            window.posthog?.capture("resume_clicked", { source: "about" });
        });
    document
        .getElementById("github-profile-link")
        ?.addEventListener("click", function () {
            window.posthog?.capture("github_profile_clicked", {
                source: "about",
            });
        });
    document
        .getElementById("linkedin-profile-link")
        ?.addEventListener("click", function () {
            window.posthog?.capture("linkedin_profile_clicked", {
                source: "about",
            });
        });
</script>
